@node History "Script History"


@{b}History@{ub}


	This is a new section as of February 1999. I felt I needed it to keep track of 
what I had done to the script moreso for myself than for any other reason.


	Mar 04/99 v1.2


	-  Finally got the byte offset for width and height of GIFs. This should
work for 99.9 % of GIFs in existence. It also works for animGIFs because (I
think) I am reading the logical screen width and height of the window that the
image should be displayed in which for most applications is equal to the image
size. Note: You know, you really shouldn't use GIFs anyway because of the
stupid copyright thing. PNGs are much easier to work with (ya I know there
isn't an animPNG but isn't MNG supposed to correct that?) and they look just as
nice.


	Feb 21/99 v1.1


	-  my am I in a programming mode or what? :)

	-  the ALT tag no longer appears if 'Cancel' is selected. I did this to
save that ever precious commodity known as bandwidth. Yup, you now save a whole
six bytes versus my old code.

	-  I have incorporated the PNG format and it was easier than I thought.
Viewtek is not used - I have figured out how to read the information directly
from the picture file. This is proving to be more difficult for JPGs and GIFs.

	-  I decided to stay with RexxReqTools because it offers better formatting
of the requesters. The <REQUESTCHOICE> and <REQUESTFILE> programs in AmigaOS
3.1 do not allow for the requester to be centered on the screen.


	Feb 20/99


	-  added the option of having no ALIGNment for the picture.

	-  fixed a problem with the picture file reference path. A '/' was prefixing the file 
path/name. This may still cause a problem when the graphics files are not in
either the same or a sub-directory as the HTML file.

	-  found out that there are problems with ANIMGIFs and PNGs. I will work on
this in future.

	-  general layout and formatting cleanup of Guide file <this file>.

@endnode

@node Future "Future"


@{b}Future@{ub}


	Maybe add some more tag variables like HSPACE and VSPACE.


	Get rid of the dependance on Viewtek. I know that AREXX can read the
information from the picture file itself. I just wrote the script quickly using
Viewtek because it was easier and because I am still learning how to read file
info in AREXX. However, the Viewtek part of the script is the quickest part of
it so this may take a while to happen.


PNG and GIF are now supported without Viewtek. See @{" Usage " link use} or @{" History " link history}.

@endnode

